This paper deals with the optimization of large-scale distributed computing systems, which involves the coordination of multiple machines to perform parallel computation. This topic is closely related to several sub-fields of computer science, including Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Control Systems (cs.SY), Performance Analysis (cs.PF), and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). Given the focus on scheduling policies and resource usage, cs.DC and cs.DS are the most likely categories, followed by cs.SY, cs.PF, and cs.NI.
